Governor Samuel Ortom has approved the appointment of Emmanuel Tama as the vice chairman of Lobi stars Football Club of Makurdi. Tama takes over from Mike Idoko who was relieved of his position last week. Tama started his football career in Benue state with famous BCC Lion FC of Gboko, later moved abroad and continued his football across Europe and America. He is a FIFA license agent with football coaching licence. There was wild jubilations among supporters of the Makurdi premier league club when news of his appointment was announced. From now He is easy going and disciplinarian who wants thing done right.